description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the Cancer Services Team based at Leighton Hospital. As a team, Cancer Services work to ensure that all patients referred on a suspected cancer pathway are seen, supported and treated as timely as possible, ensuring that we provide “&lt;em&gt;an outstanding experience for every patient”, &lt;/em&gt;as per our Trust’s values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is pivotal in the Trust’s ability to consistently achieve the national cancer waiting times standards, ensuring that our patients are seen rapidly i.e. within 7 days or less of their referral and receive their treatment within 62 days. Mid Cheshire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust consistently performs to a high standard and ensures all patients on a cancer journey are diagnosed and treated in a timely manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role would suit a well organised, dedicated person with excellent prioritisation skills, who enjoys working in a fast-paced environment and would like to make a difference to cancer patient’s experience. The post holder will establish key working relationships with all members of the administrative and clinical teams including nursing and medical staff, allied health professional and support workers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be responsible for supporting weekly MDT meetings, of which you will help to prepare, facilitate and record outcomes of each patient discussion via the Somerset cancer database in a live environment. As a Cancer Pathway Coordinator you will ensure concise and daily tracking of each step in a patient pathway, data quality and completeness, expediting appointments/visits ensuring patients are not delayed at any point in their pathway&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good knowledge of medical terminology including types of cancer, diagnostics and treatment options would be desirable. Good data inputting, extraction and interpretation skills are essential. Advanced keyboard skills would be beneficial for data inputting required for this role. Ability to communicate clearly with a range of stakeholders is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: Annette Lewis, Cancer Performance Manager on (27)3609.&lt;/p&gt;
